column1: "Amazon Prime is a paid subscription program from Amazon that gives users access to additional services otherwise unavailable or available at a premium to regular Amazon customers. Services include same
column2: one or two-day delivery and streaming music and video.\n"

Amazon reported that Prime had more than 150 million subscribers worldwide.
\n"

column1: "The Prime Video service debuted on September 7
column2: 2006 as Amazon Unbox in the United States. On September 4
column4: the service was renamed Amazon Video on Demand. The Unbox name still refers to the local program
column5: which as of August 2014 is no longer available for downloading purchased instant videos. On February 22
column7: the service rebranded as Amazon Instant Video."
